cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SY

This paper focuses on the use of mobile-edge computing (MEC) and unmanned aerial vehicle base stations (UAV-BSs) for online data processing in IoT. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes an online determination policy based on Lyapunov Optimization, which involves optimization and control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category as well. The paper also applies deep reinforcement learning for path planning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of effective path planning, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
